task_description: Facing the building to your North-East (approx. 30°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: The building is centered in view but the full height may not be visible at pitch 0°; rotating up will reveal the roofline to measure from ground to top.
To measure the full height, I need to see both the base and roof; rotating down 60° from current pitch will reveal the ground level for triangulation.
Current pitch is 60° down, obscuring the building's structure; rotating up 60° to pitch 0° will align the view with the building's base for height estimation.

The building's roof is visible at 60° up pitch, but the base is obscured; rotating down 60° to pitch 0° will align the view with the ground level for accurate height triangulation using the known distance of ~10m.
The building's base is visible at pitch 0° and roof at ~60° up; with a distance of 10m, height ≈ 10 * tan(60°) = 17.3m.
